result.text:
Only one Vice Chancellor is from the SC community, one from the ST community, seven from the OBC community, and only 29.21% of the teaching staff in 45 Central Universities is from the SC, ST, or OBC community.

In 45 Central Universities, there were 8386 in General category. However, just 1306, 568, 1740 were from SC, ST, OBC categories, showing lesser representation in Teaching staff. The overall representation in Teaching staff is enclosed below,

General- 67.78%
SC-10.56%
ST-4.59%
OBC - 14.06%

Even today, Just 29.21% reservation is what is achieved for SC, ST and OBC in teaching staff

In terms of non-teaching staff in all 45 central universities, there were 16132 from General out of 22096 employees. However, only 2063, 1186, and 2342 employees were from the SC, ST, OBC category. 
The overall representation in Non-Teaching staff is as under,

General- 73%
SC-9.33%
ST-5.36%
OBC - 10.6%

Even today, Just 27% reservation is what is achieved for SC, ST and OBC in non teaching staff..

This shows a negligible representation of SC, ST, OBC in all 45 central universities.

#centraluniversities #ugc #reservation #merit
